These, Tychiades, though they are perpetually talking about fortitude, and hackneying the name of virtue, are more timid and cowardly even than our orators: who ever heard of a philosopher dying in battle ? they either never fought at all, or if they did, took the first opportunity to run away. Antisthenes, Diogenes, Crates, zeno, Plato, AEsehines‚ Aristotle, and the whole tribe of them, never so much as saw an engagement.
